=============================================
KGGZ: The GGZ Gaming Zone Core Client for KDE
=============================================

KGGZ is one of the GGZ frontends. That means, it is intended to be used as a central
place for players to gather, chat and play games.
This is now version 0.0.4pre6 of KGGZ. It is distributed under GNU GPL license conditions.

News - what has changed?:
-------------------------
 => this section has gone into doc/ChangeLog.
Please have a look into the CVS changelog for more accurate information.

 * * * important news: this is _not_ the working version. It is rather a rebirth of kggz :) * * *

Requirements:
-------------
-Xlib for the beep :)
-Qt 2.2.1
-KDE 2.x (kdelibs should be sufficient)
-KHTML (optionally) for the browser
-Qt network extension (optionally) for FTP
-the GGZ libs of course

Installation:
-------------
Just run ./autogen.sh. This should do everything for you.
During the installation process you will be prompted for your
root password.
For more detailed installation instructions, please have a look into doc/INSTALL.

Directory structure:
--------------------
/		- sources
/images/	- images for kggz
/images/games/	- icons for all game modules
/images/icons/	- menu & widget icons
/images/themes/ - theme images and descriptions
/images/wm/	- window manager decoration, e.g. start menu & desktop
/doc/		- documentation
/doc/html	- tbd: detailed programmer information on kggz
/help/		- local in-client help files
/po/		- i18n files

Installation structure:
-----------------------
~/.kde/share/locale/l10n/...		- i18n .mo files
~/.kde/share/icons/			- icons for KDE
~/.kde/share/applnk/Games/ggz/		- KDE menu entries
~/.kde/share/mimelnk/application/	- Zone entry
destdir/bin/				- executable
destdir/share/kggz/...			- core client data

You can do the following things:
--------------------------------
-invoke the server and/or connect to it
-chat
-browse the rooms list
-use the chat with all commands
**attempt to join or launch a game
**see your network lag
-browse the internet :-)
-download game modules
**configure game modules
**talk with grubby
** means: todo, but already prepared

You can't do yet:
-----------------
-play games

What else needs to be done?
---------------------------
-documentation (html)
-port some of the games to kde (although one can use gtk+ games, of course)
-more more games for ggz!!!

